				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hercules-rockefeller" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2314402); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2314402&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250358" alt="Hercules Rockefeller" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2314402)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hercules-rockefeller" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2314402); return false;" >Hercules Rockefeller</a></span> <span class="odate time_1462642305 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 May 2016 17:31</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2504960">
									

<p>Damn, this is really good.</p>
<p>Not only does this fit in seamlessly with the original article, it actually adds to it, without spoiling the mystery. And there were some fantastically creepy sentences in there, especially:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The ladder is only twelve rungs (I've been counting for a couple years now)</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>There's a force, but there's no force to really sense in there. It's empty in there. That's what I hope for.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>I catch a glimpse of my parents, sleeping with their heads buried into the wall</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't know what that last one means, but <em>shit</em>&#8230;</p>
<p>But my favorite has got to be this throwaway line here:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>(did the door ever have a lock? I can't see why)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Such a subtle allusion to that sense you get in the original article that the parents <em>did something</em> to her.</p>
<p>My only criticism is that the first few paragraphs feel a bit info-dumpy to me - I get that the tale is being connected to the original article, but I think a few of the details that are reiterated from SCP- 2740 aren't necessary (like mentioning what her job is, for example).</p>
<p>+1</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;A&nbsp;few&nbsp;grammar&nbsp;nitpicks</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;nitpicks</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>Maybe if I at least think like that, part of the blame wouldn't be on me.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>should be &quot;won't be on me&quot;; alternately, you could change &quot;think&quot; to &quot;thought&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>to clear the air up and make things better for the both of us.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>suggest &quot;for all of us&quot; since you're referring to three people.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I snagged a few gifts for my parents and siblings on the way there, and it took me almost half a day of driving to get there.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>suggest removing the first &quot;there&quot;, since it's unnecessary and you'd avoid repeating it.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Everyone had acted like my existence was never there to begin with.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>suggest &quot;like I'd never existed to begin with&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The attic is still there, too.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>should be &quot;was still there&quot;</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

